abstract: In the age of quizzes, “The Great British Baking Show” and access to experts all over the world, we don’t have to settle for the traditional televised debate format.
snippet: In the age of quizzes, “The Great British Baking Show” and access to experts all over the world, we don’t have to settle for the traditional televised debate format.
lead_paragraph: The candidate debates have become such a fixture of presidential elections in the United States that it’s easy to imagine them as inevitable and unchangeable components of our democratic process. But as we examine our democratic traditions in this fraught campaign cycle, we should take a step back and consider whether, in this age of online quizzes, audience-voted competition shows and Reddit AMAs, we could find better ways to figure out which politicians we want to vote for.

headline_main: Presidential Debates Could Be Much More Imaginative

abstract: The pageant’s continuous ratings decline reflects a long history of criticism from both liberals and conservatives.
snippet: The pageant’s continuous ratings decline reflects a long history of criticism from both liberals and conservatives.
lead_paragraph: On Sept. 8, 1945, just a few months after the German surrender in World War II, my mother, Bess Myerson, became the first — and to this day, only — Jewish Miss America. When you look back on that moment in history, it might be easy to imagine that postwar sympathies helped my mother secure the crown.

abstract: A Michigan man who has been imprisoned in Russia on spying charges for nearly a year has lost his job with an automotive parts supplier in a corporate restructuring, a move his brother has denounced.
snippet: A Michigan man who has been imprisoned in Russia on spying charges for nearly a year has lost his job with an automotive parts supplier in a corporate restructuring, a move his brother has denounced.
lead_paragraph: AUBURN HILLS, Mich. — A Michigan man who has been imprisoned in Russia on spying charges for nearly a year has lost his job with an automotive parts supplier in a corporate restructuring, a move his brother has denounced.
headline_main: US Man Jailed in Russia on Spying Charges Loses Job
headline_print_headline: US Man Jailed in Russia on Spying Charges Loses Job

abstract: A conservative talk-radio outlet in Denver canceled a married couple’s show after the husband wished on the air for something to draw attention away from impeachment.
snippet: A conservative talk-radio outlet in Denver canceled a married couple’s show after the husband wished on the air for something to draw attention away from impeachment.
lead_paragraph: The conservative married couple’s afternoon talk show on KNUS in Denver had been going for a half-hour on Tuesday when the husband made a remark that alarmed his wife, stunned their listeners — and soon cost them their jobs.

abstract: California prosecutors found no evidence of animal cruelty or other crimes during an investigation into a spike in horse deaths at Santa Anita Park racetrack over the past year, according to a report issued Thursday.
snippet: California prosecutors found no evidence of animal cruelty or other crimes during an investigation into a spike in horse deaths at Santa Anita Park racetrack over the past year, according to a report issued Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — California prosecutors found no evidence of animal cruelty or other crimes during an investigation into a spike in horse deaths at Santa Anita Park racetrack over the past year, according to a report issued Thursday.
headline_main: Prosecutor Finds No Crime in Santa Anita Horse Racing Deaths
headline_print_headline: Prosecutor Finds No Crime in Santa Anita Horse Racing Deaths

abstract: Jona Rechnitz was arrested on corruption charges in New York and then became a star witness. His testimony led to the conviction of several officials.
snippet: Jona Rechnitz was arrested on corruption charges in New York and then became a star witness. His testimony led to the conviction of several officials.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio called him a “liar and a felon.”

headline_main: ‘Liar,’ and Star Witness in City Graft Cases, Gets 10-Month Sentence

abstract: With government funding set to lapse Friday, the Senate passed the $1.4 trillion deal in time for lawmakers to leave for a scheduled holiday break.
snippet: With government funding set to lapse Friday, the Senate passed the $1.4 trillion deal in time for lawmakers to leave for a scheduled holiday break.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress gave final approval on Thursday to $1.4 trillion in federal spending, staving off a lapse in government funding for the remainder of the fiscal year and delivering the legislation to President Trump in a year-end flurry of bipartisan compromise.

abstract: A Michigan research institute accused of failing to disclose Chinese government grants received by two of its researchers has reached a $5.5 million settlement, the Justice Department announced Thursday.
snippet: A Michigan research institute accused of failing to disclose Chinese government grants received by two of its researchers has reached a $5.5 million settlement, the Justice Department announced Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Michigan research institute accused of failing to disclose Chinese government grants received by two of its researchers has reached a $5.5 million settlement, the Justice Department announced Thursday.
headline_main: Institute to Pay $5.5M for Not Disclosing Chinese Grants
headline_print_headline: Institute to Pay $5.5M for Not Disclosing Chinese Grants

abstract: Suggested reading from critics and editors at The New York Times.
snippet: Suggested reading from critics and editors at The New York Times.
lead_paragraph: Eccentrics, obsessives and big personalities dominate this week’s nonfiction. We recommend the memoir of a professional foodie and the biography of a secretive investor who was determined to beat the market — he succeeded, phenomenally — as well as the life of an influential leftist congresswoman from the 1970s and the lives of three sisters who pushed their way to the center of modern Chinese history. We also have the biography of a German Jew who fled Nazism but returned as an American spy, and a dual biography of the ancient Romans Pliny the Elder and Pliny the Younger. (The elder was the obsessive one: As our review points out, he was so intrepid that he died “while trying to inspect an active volcano.”)
